ates, mainly   Denis  , in the continental Europe) seems to have been largely due to French influence. The feminine form <i>Dionysia</i> (in vernacular English likewise <i>Den(n)is</i>) is also found, and some examples of the surname may originate from it.","English: from Middle English <i>deneis</i>, a variant of <i>danais</i> ‘Danish’, with the vowel influenced by Middle English <i>denshe</i> (Old English <i>denisc</i>). Compare   Dence  .","Irish (mainly Dublin and Cork): of the same origin as 1 and 2 above, sometimes an alternative form to   Donohue   but more often to   McDonough  , since the personal name <i>Donnchadh</i> was Anglicized as <i>Donough</i> or <i>Denis</i>."]},{"name":"Addonizio","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Carmine, Olympia, Ornella, Salvatore.","Italian: from the personal name   Dionisio  , with the patronymic prefix <i>a-</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Dionisia was born in 1205. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert de Burghill."},"et":{"1205–":"1205–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1228–1272":"1228–1272","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1228":"1228","1205":"1205","about 1228":"umbes 1228","1200":"1200","1272":"1272","Burghill, Herefordshire, England":"Burghill, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"1205–":"1205–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1228–1272":"1228–1272","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1205":"1205","about 1228":"noin 1228","1200":"1200","1272":"1272","Burghill, Herefordshire, England":"Burghill, Herefordshire, England"},"fr":{"1205–":"1205–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1228–1272":"1228–1272","1205–Female":"1205–Décédée","1228":"1228","1205":"1205","about 1228":"environ 1228","1200":"1200","1272":"1272","Burghill, Herefordshire, England":"Burghill, Herefordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Dionisia est née en 1205. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Robert de Burghill."},"de":{"1205–":"1205–Verstorben","1200–Male":"1200–Verstorben","1228–1272":"1228–1272","1205–Female":"1205–Verstorben","1228